1. **Purpose**

Development of a new website realspiedzivojums.lv in accordance with the conditions listed below, replacing the currently visible version of the website with the new page.

The conditions listed below are considered **the first phase of website development** . The following main functionality is created within the first phase:

- Website code base with secure, fast code and a management system convenient for the Customer;  
- Special, attractive visual design of the website;  
- A set of pages necessary for informing customers;  
- Ordering the offered services, including making payments and registering transactions;  
- Individual client offices with authorized access;Rēķini, Līgums, pasākuma foto. Ieviešot otro etapu-CRM, te var būt korekcijas.

2. **General requirements**

   1. ## **Language** {#language}

**Content and management system:** in Latvian.

**Programming language** : PHP, preferably Laravel  (Next JS)framework. The program code includes explanatory notes, which will make it easier for other programmers to navigate in the future.

2. ## **Usability** {#usability}

**Speed:** The mobile version of the landing page has a “Performance” score of over 70 in the Google Lighthouse test.

**Other indices:**

- The “ *Accessibility* ” and “ *Best practices* ” indicators in the Google Lighthouse test exceed 93  (90).  
- The *SEO* score in the Google Lighthouse test exceeds 98 (šo neesmu lietojis, nemācēšu pateikt kritērijus)  Te ir pēdējais, ko esam nodevuši: ![][image1]  
-   
- .

**Visual design:** a visually appealing page whose design exudes a sense of corporate environment, lightness, dynamism, and good mood.

**Availability:**

- Full page functionality and design consistency across all commonly used screen sizes using responsive design principles.  
- The page is also easy to use without additional adjustments for people with visual impairments such as the more common types of color blindness (poor perception of green and red) and blurred vision.  
- The page includes the necessary *on-site SEO* principles and data, including SEO-optimized page titles and keywords, other necessary meta-information, schema.org parameters, SEO-optimized media file names. There is an option to add and edit this data in the *admin panel.*  
- Google Analytics or Google Tags.  
- A "Submit suggestions for improvements" form in the footer so users can submit suggestions for improvements to the website and its content.

  3. ## **Security** {#security}

- Authorized *admin* access (email and password)  
- Authorized customer access to their data (email and password)  
- Automatic full website *back-up* (once a month, for the last three months) and *admin* interface so that the Customer can always revert to an earlier version of the website.  
- Automated log file creation that documents admin, customer, and potential other access to the website's admin panel and/or code.

3. **Public part ( *front-end* )**

   1. ## **Navigation** {#navigation}

- The navigation included in the header has the following links:  
  1) **For groups** (takes you to the relevant page, where events suitable for groups are selected)  
  2) **For schools** (takes you to the relevant page where activities suitable for schools/classes are selected)  
  3) **For families** (takes you to the relevant page, where activities suitable for schools/classes are selected)  
  4) **About us** (takes you to the “about us” page)  
     * **Events** (events, venues, additional services)  
     * **Tips** (blog)  
     * **Experience** (portfolio)  
     * **Gallery**  
     * **Charity**  
  5) **Apply\!** (application form, see below, application process infographic)

  2. ## **Header** {#header}

- The initial version uses the same type of header on all pages.  
- The header includes: Customer's logo, navigation, login button, Customer's social media accounts, phone number.  
- The header leaves room for a language switcher (in the future).  
- It is recommended to create two bars for the header – the top (contact information, entrance to the client area) and the bottom (logo and navigation).

  3. ## **Footer** {#footer}

- Two lanes  
- The top one contains administrative information, which can be arranged in two or three columns:  
  1) Logo with a link to the home page. Contact information, property information (or a link to the property information page);  
  2) Links to the sections “About us”, “Charity”, “How to register for an event?”, “Frequently asked questions”, “Privacy policy”, “Terms and conditions”. Form “Submit suggestions for improvements”;  
  3) Entrance to the client area;  
- The bottom bar contains links to available service types broken down by target audience type.

  4. ## **WhatsApp communication element** {#whatsapp-communication-element}

- In the lower right corner, there is a floating *permanent* element that is visible on all pages – the WhatsApp icon.  
- When you click on it, a WhatsApp dialog window opens, which the user can close again.  
- Any user of the website can start a conversation by entering their phone number. The phone number is validated and checked to see if the user is not a bot.  
- Any user communication is individual and visible only to the participants in the conversation.  
- The Customer receives messages from this WhatsApp dialogue to their WhatsApp account.  
- At the beginning of the conversation, the customer is sent a greeting and a pre-prepared message (for example, a current upcoming event). It is possible to edit or change it in the admin panel.  
- Conversations are saved and available in the Admin panel ( *see description in point 3* ).

  5. ## **Introduction page** {#introduction-page}

The following vertically arranged information sections:

- On the initial screen (before scrolling, *above the scroll* ): visually appealing image or video, focus text (e.g. current “Top events for businesses and families from A to Z”), call-to-action button (e.g. “Register for an event”)  
- **Special offers** – 1 or more special offers (e.g. archery with 10% discount) with a countdown. Image with a short description.  
- **News** – 3 to 6 most recent publications on the website that have been tagged with the “news” tag. Each news item has an illustrative image, publication date, title, beginning of the text or text excerpt. Links to the news page.  
- **Events** divided by target audience type: “Schools”, “Groups”, “Families” with links to the relevant pages. For each target audience type – an illustrative image and introductory text.  
- **How to apply for the event?** Informative infographic and link to a page with an explanation.  
- **Statistics of completed work** . Use sample.  
- **About us** . Introductory information about the company and its face – Sandija Krastiņa. For example, an expressive image on one side and text on the other. Link to the “About us” page.  
- **Charity** . Illustrative images, links to events, and a link to a page about the charity.  
- **Customer Reviews** . 3 to 6 most recent customer reviews and a link to the reviews page.


  6. ## **Other pages** {#other-pages}

     1. **Event type pages**  
- Hierarchy:  
  1) The main event page, from which pages are available divided by category and divided by target audience, "how to register for an event" (can be taken to a separate page with more detailed information), event venues (will take you to a separate page with more detailed information), additional services (will take you to a separate page with more detailed information), as well as a tag cloud.  
  2) Set up an event type filter, similar to [https://oratastic.eu/lydene/](https://oratastic.eu/lydene/) \- but at three levels (you need to click three selections).  
  3) Event category pages. Static introductory text and image, as well as a list of events that match the category, selected based on the tag. "How to register an event" section (can lead to a separate page with more detailed information).  
  4) Audience pages. Static introductory text and image, as well as a list of events relevant to the audience, selected based on the tag. “How to register for an event” section (can lead to a separate page with more detailed information).  
  5) Individual event description pages (around 70). Event description and illustrative material, all events have a uniform format. Tags. Opportunity to apply for each event.  
       
     2. **News**  
- It is dynamically generated by adding pages with the tag “news”;  
- The 12-14 most recent pages are displayed with the option to expand the list ("show more") until all the news is visible. The first (or specially selected) pages can be highlighted larger, occupying the entire width of the screen.  
- Each individual page has links to paid services.

  3. **Tips (blog)**  
- It is dynamically generated by adding pages with the tag “blog” (or “tips”);  
- Tag cloud (internal to this type);  
- The 12-14 most recent pages are displayed with the option to expand the list (show more) until all pages are visible. The first (or specially selected) pages can be highlighted larger, taking up the entire width of the screen.  
- Each individual page has links to paid services.

  4. **Experience/Portfolio**  
- A single, single page about the company's experience and statistics.  
- List of completed activities (perhaps with a logo for each)  
- The 12-14 most recent customer reviews are included with the option to extend the list (show more) until all reviews (including videos) are visible.

  5. **Charity**  
- It is dynamically generated by adding pages with the tag “charity”;  
- Current;  
- What has been accomplished;  
- The 12-14 most recent pages are displayed with the option to expand the list (show more) until all pages are visible. The first (or specially selected) pages can be highlighted larger, taking up the entire width of the screen.

  6. **About us**  
- A unified, single page about the company's values, history, and staff.  
- Sections “Tips”, “Charity” and “Experience” are included with links to the relevant pages.  
- Properties.

  7. **Administrative pages**  
- How to register for an event.  
- Frequently asked questions.  
- Privacy policy.  
- Terms and conditions.  
- 404 page.

  7. ## **Filters and tags** {#filters-and-tags}

- The information posted on the website can be selected according to predefined filter settings by assigning defined tags to the pages;  
- The Contractor creates an opportunity for the Customer to define such tags themselves and, accordingly, assign the defined tags to pages.  
- Each page can be assigned none, one, or many tags.  
- Possible tags:  
  1) Seasons;  
  2) Types of locations (indoors, outdoors);  
  3) Target audience (companies, young people, children under 4 years old, children 5-8 years old, children 9-12 years old, adults, organizations, families);  
  4) Purpose of the event (unification, team building, entertainment, sports, training);  
  5) Event category (team, individual, active, leisure).

  8. ## **Fillable forms and communication** {#fillable-forms-and-communication}

- A uniform form with multiple levels of detail.  
- Available from different parts of the website with different names, but takes you to the same form.  
    
  1. **First page of the form**  
- First name, last name\*  
- Phone\*  
- Email\*  
- Event target audience (groups, schools, family, holiday, *dropdown selection* )\*  
- Event type ( *dropdown selection – already filtered, according to target audience* )\*  
- Approximate costs ( *dropdown selection* )\* (Minimum amount 550 – if the client names a lower amount – a notice that the event will not be held for such an amount\!)  
- Menu: “Continue filling in” / “Submit now\!”  
- Note at the bottom that the part has already been submitted for any choice.  
  2. **Second form page**  
- Number of participants ( *dropdown selection* )\*  
- Dates ( *dropdown selection* )\*  
- Duration ( *dropdown selection* )  
- Location ( *dropdown selection* )  
- Apply for one of the ready-made programs (menu with an illustrated panel, one of the choices is “Create your own unique event”)  
- Free description ( *240 characters* )  
- Menu “Continue filling in more details” / “Submit now\!”

This is where the branching occurs :

1) If the customer has selected “special need”, the following options will dynamically open at the bottom: “Continue to fill in more details” / “Submit now\!”  
   2) If the client has selected a certain type of program, one option dynamically opens at the bottom: “Submit my request\!” The client's additional needs are clarified in a direct conversation.  
      3. **Third page (special needs) form**  
- Difficulty level ( *dropdown selection* )  
- Preferred venue ( *dropdown selection* )  
- Catering ( *dropdown selection* )  
- Desired additional services ( *multiple choice selection – all options are transparent* )  
- Team competition (yes/no). If “yes” is selected, the following menus appear dynamically:  
  1) Team size ( *dropdown selection* )  
  2) Difficulty level ( *dropdown selection* )  
  3) Reward ( *dropdown selection* )  
  4) Services ( *multiple choice* )  
- “Submit my request\!”  
  4. **“Your request has been submitted” page**  
- After submitting the form, a notification page will automatically open with the text “Your request has been submitted”  
- Additional information on how to communicate further. If it's urgent – call\!  
- Submitted request information.  
- *The request is sent both to the Customer's email address and to the customer's own email address specified.*

  9. ## **Social networks** {#social-networks}

- Links to the Customer's social media accounts are available in the header of the website.  
- Each page has the option to share its link on social networks.

  10. ## **Client's "office"** {#client's-"office"}

- Each contract and communication email concluded by the Customer is registered in the website management system.  
- The system automatically generates a special access code for each contract, which, after entering the contract information, is automatically sent to the client's email and is also visible in the website management system.  
- Each customer can log in to the website by entering their email address and access code. The input is in the header or footer (or both).  
- In the client cabinet, there is an option to make payments (currently – only advance payments of 550 EUR) using Stripe. All services provided have the same amount – 550 EUR, advance payment.  
- The client cabinet includes the following information:  
  1) Contract information  
  2) Settlement documents (invoice, bill of lading)  
  3) Event gallery.

4. **Management system ( *CMS* )**

   1. ## **Pages** {#pages}

- New Page Button  
- Overview of existing pages in table form, each page can be opened and edited individually. You cannot edit in the table, you must open it. Columns in the table:  
  1) Slug  
  2) Title  
  3) Date, time  
  4) First words of the meta description  
  5) Status.  
- Information to include on each page:  
  1) Title – written by myself  
  2) Slug – self-recorded  
  3) (Content) still to be expanded  
  4) Featured image – self-selected  
  5) Meta description (160 characters, traffic light principle) – you must write it yourself  
  6) Date, time – automatically generated  
  7) Status – publish\!/draft/archive. Selecting “Publish\!” will publish the page.  
  8) Tags/tags.  
  9) Notes (notes related to this page that are not visible to customers, e.g. work that still needs to be done).  
  10) Delete (with warning).


  2. ## **Media** {#media}

- Images and documents are managed here.  
- Videos are stored elsewhere and are not manageable through this panel.  
- Automatically reduce image size.  
- “Add new” button at the top  
- Table:  
  1) Thumbnail – a small preview of an image  
  2) File name.  
  3) Category – Internal categories are created for images, allowing you to quickly select certain types of images.  
  4) Alt text – editable  
  5) Date – when the image was uploaded  
  6) Size – automatically calculated  
  7) Link – a link to the image that should be included on the pages where it will be used  
  8) Delete – option to delete the image. When pressed, a warning and (possible) links to places where the image has been used appear.  
- Bulk upload: gallery upload \+ access code for client galleries. These galleries are available for 6 months and are only accessible by entering the relevant code.

  3. ## **WhatsApp communication** {#whatsapp-communication}

- Every WhatsApp conversation that takes place through the website is saved.  
- Overview in table form, entries with the latest activities at the top:  
  1) ID – automatically generated  
  2) Customer phone number – the one entered by the customer is used  
  3) Start date, time – automatically generated, start of conversation.  
  4) Last conversation time – automatically generated, time of last conversation.  
  5) First name/last name – optional, optional.  
  6) The first words of the correspondence.  
- The table can be sorted by first/last name, tenses.  
- Clicking on the corresponding line opens the entire WhatsApp conversation.  
- Only the client can start a list (from scratch, from the very beginning).  
- Lists can also be made here, in the management system.  
- Editing an automated message.

  4. ## **Customer management** {#customer-management}

- Overview of customer contracts in tabular form:  
  1) ID – automatically generated  
  2) First name/last name – required  
  3) Company \- must be entered  
  4) Email – required  
  5) Event type \- must be entered  
  6) contract number – must be entered  
  7) amount – to be entered  
  8) date – the date of conclusion of the contract, must be entered  
  9) access code – automatically generated  
  10) “Send” – a button after entering data. When pressed, it asks whether to really send. Sends the contract access code to the client along with a pre-prepared letter text. After sending, the button changes color and says “send again?”.  
  11) active/completed etc. – dropdown.  
- You can open an information page for each customer (if all the columns in the table do not match, all the information is available here \- we can reschedule it). Stripe billing information and access to Stripe are also available here.  
- The oldest clients are at the bottom, the newest ones are at the top.  
- Top row empty – when filled, the next empty row appears above for the next customer.  
- If the customer's email is repeated (repeated transaction), the system offers to use the same access code as the previous time. If the administrator agrees, the customer is sent the same access code and has access to information for multiple events in his customer account.  
- Search / Filter. Filters : date ranges, active/inactive, amount ranges, event type.  
- Export to Excel.

  5. ## **Administration** {#administration}

- Page admin table (one level for now):  
  1) ID, automatically generated  
  2) First name, last name  
  3) Email  
  4) Send password button – when pressed, the active password is sent to your email. A different one will be sent next time.  
- Access info, table:  
  1) Admin  
  2) Access time  
  3) Last page where changes were made  
- Backup:  
  1) Is there an automatic backup once a month?  
  2) The last two backups are saved.  
  3) The possibility of returning to one of them.

5. **Work execution**

   1. ## **Stages of work** {#stages-of-work}

1) The Client shall submit sample information for each page type specified in Sections 3.5 (Introductory Page), 3.6 (Other Pages) and 3.8 (Fill-in Forms).  
2) The contractor develops *a wireframe* – a design sample for each page type. Vienojāmies, ka izstrādās uzreiz dizaina paraugus Galvenajai lapai, kategorijas un produktu lapām, visdrīzāk, būtu nepieciešams arī aizpildāmajām formām un aprēķinu sadaļai. Ja ir vēl kāda ļoti unikāla lapa, tad tai arī, bet aprēķinā ir šīs lapas. Vai nepieciešams vēl kādu lapu dizainēt? Ja jā, tad jārēķinās ar papildus budžetu.  
3) After developing the design samples, the Contractor develops the full page content on the temporary website.  
4) The Client submits to the Contractor the information to be included on all pages, the Contractor copies the data to be used from the previous website.  
5) The contractor tests the functionality of the page and makes improvements.  
6) The customer, on their part, tests the page and recommends improvements.  
7) The contractor is making final improvements before moving.  
8) The Contractor trains the Client on how to use the site.  
9) After the Customer's acceptance, the Contractor replaces the old page with the new one.  
10) The contractor redirects the old page addresses to the new website.

    2. ## **Technical support** {#technical-support}

- The contractor shall eliminate the discovered deficiencies for a further 6 (2) months after the final settlement of the contract without additional payment.  
- The Contractor advises the Client on the use of the site for up to 2 hours per month at no additional charge  2 mēnešus. 

  3. ## ***Potential development of the page*** {#potential-development-of-the-page}

- *In the future, outside the scope of this agreement, the following functionality may be developed for the page:*  
  1) *Online store with a payment system included in the website functionality;*  
  2) *Online calendar;*  
  3) *Customer management system (CRM);*  
  4) *Warehouse management system;*  
  5) *Ticket sales system / Purchase of competition participation;*  
  6) *Artificial intelligence support for customers;*  
  7) *Mobile application(s) (photo, auto orienteering, rallies, questions/answers, QR code orienteering).*

6. **Customer's obligations**

   1. ## **Basic principles** {#basic-principles}

- In order to achieve the best possible result as quickly as possible, the Parties shall cooperate collegially in developing and testing the website design, as well as selecting the elements and content to be placed on it.  
- In situations where the Client has not submitted the elements and texts to be placed on the website, the Contractor will leave an unfilled space, informing the Client about this. The website will be designed in such a way that the Client can permanently fill in these unfilled spaces.

  2. ## **Planning the page structure** {#planning-the-page-structure}

- The client designs the page structure and decides which pages need to be created.  
- The Contractor shall inform the Client of the necessary decisions in this regard.  
- The customer decides how the information placed on the page will be filtered and what tags will be used.  
- The Contractor shall inform the Customer of the necessary decisions in this regard, including recommending the desired filter types and tags.

  3. ## **Pictures and videos** {#pictures-and-videos}

- The customer provides the developer with images and videos to be placed on the website.  
- The Contractor informs the Client about the necessary and still missing images and information about them.  
- Images and videos must meet minimum quality requirements, which the Contractor shall inform the Customer about in each individual case.  
- The Client must submit additional information about each of the images and videos so that the Contractor can add the necessary “alt” tags and captions.  
- The developer only needs to edit and process the images and videos that are necessary for the artistic design of the page.

  4. ## **Texts** {#texts}

- The customer provides the developer with texts to be placed on the website, including title texts, tag names, and meta-texts. Izpildītājs ievieto pamata saturu līdz mājaslapas nodošanai. Pēc tam Pasūtītājs saturu ievieto pats.   
- Izpildītājs Pasūtītājs ir atbildīgs par pilna satura iesūtīšanuinformē Pasūtītāju par nepieciešamajiem un vēl trūkstošajiem tekstiem.  
- The Contractor may correct any errors noticed in the text, but this is not the Contractor's obligation.

Nepieciešams papildināt par automātisko aprēķinu un apmaksu.
